32:52.871 --> 32:55.541
am I right?

32:55.541 --> 32:57.709
Wow. That's definitely hot.

32:57.709 --> 32:59.245
It's...

32:59.245 --> 33:01.113
Very hot.

33:01.113 --> 33:03.282
Right? Damn it.

33:03.282 --> 33:06.152
It would have been so epic!

33:06.152 --> 33:08.154
Oh. Okay.

33:08.154 --> 33:09.821
Oh, I'm done with the spinning.

33:09.821 --> 33:12.391
Spinning I'm done with.

33:13.759 --> 33:16.762
Hey, so, mack was totally hot.

33:16.762 --> 33:19.131
Hey, I knew it.

33:19.131 --> 33:20.466
I knew...

33:20.466 --> 33:23.469
You, my friend, are incar...

33:24.803 --> 33:27.173
Incorr... corrigible!

33:27.173 --> 33:28.407
- Shannon...
- Incorrigible.

33:28.407 --> 33:29.741
Small words. Too much wine.

33:29.741 --> 33:31.109
You're dumb.

33:37.583 --> 33:39.285
Whatever. I'd top that.

33:39.285 --> 33:42.288
You talk like a boy.

33:42.288 --> 33:43.822
I am a boy.

33:45.191 --> 33:46.225
Well...

33:58.370 --> 34:00.706
I thought we agreed
no guys on this trip.

34:00.706 --> 34:04.443
No, we agreed
no "Josh" on this trip.

34:04.443 --> 34:06.612
Wow, that's not fair.

34:06.612 --> 34:08.614
Whatever. Move over.

34:08.614 --> 34:10.181
Ow.

34:12.284 --> 34:15.786
Why do you stay with him anyway?

34:15.786 --> 34:17.789
- Because I love him.
- No.

34:17.789 --> 34:21.193
- I do... I love...
- No!

34:21.193 --> 34:24.295
- I love him, Kris.
- No, you don't, Shannon.

34:30.936 --> 34:32.938
Well, he loves me.

34:32.938 --> 34:35.172
That is not the same thing.

34:36.475 --> 34:38.476
Better than the alternative.

34:38.476 --> 34:41.480
Oh, yeah, what's that?

34:41.480 --> 34:42.813
Being old.

34:42.813 --> 34:45.951
Did you hear that?

34:45.951 --> 34:49.288
You can't get out of this
that easy.

34:49.288 --> 34:51.822
No, I heard something.

34:51.822 --> 34:53.391
Shan'.

34:54.393 --> 34:55.860
More drinking,

34:55.860 --> 34:57.629
less... something.

35:09.675 --> 35:11.377
Told ya.

35:11.377 --> 35:12.944
I know I heard something.

35:12.944 --> 35:13.979
Hang on.

35:43.709 --> 35:45.411
I told no! I told you no!

36:02.027 --> 36:04.463
Charlie, please,
you have to listen to me.

36:04.463 --> 36:07.833
- Please? You gotta listen..
- I told you no!

36:34.560 --> 36:37.095
Can I help you with something?

36:37.095 --> 36:38.630
No.

36:38.630 --> 36:41.767
I was just getting
some fresh air and I...

36:41.767 --> 36:44.903
- That I saw someone...
- Saw what, darling?

36:44.903 --> 36:47.506
I thought I saw
someone on the road.

36:47.506 --> 36:49.941
I doubt you saw
anybody out there.

36:49.941 --> 36:52.778
We knock off real early
around here.

36:52.778 --> 36:54.480
Now let's get you
back to your room.

36:54.480 --> 36:56.782
No, that's okay. I got it.

37:23.642 --> 37:25.377
Kris?

37:29.114 --> 37:30.982
Kris?

37:30.982 --> 37:32.551
Kris.

37:33.519 --> 37:36.121
Kris?

37:36.121 --> 37:37.823
Kris, wake up.

37:37.823 --> 37:39.858
Kris, wake up! This isn't funny!

37:39.858 --> 37:41.993
What's with the shaking?

37:41.993 --> 37:45.030
Stop doing that. Go away.

37:55.674 --> 37:58.410
Just another
Shannon and Kris adventure.

39:00.906 --> 39:02.941
Oh, fuck.

40:54.019 --> 40:55.921
Oh, shit.

41:04.696 --> 41:06.231
Kris?

41:09.034 --> 41:11.202
Kris, time to wake up.

41:17.208 --> 41:20.679
I feel like ass, dude.

41:20.679 --> 41:23.715
I know what you mean, dude.

41:38.730 --> 41:42.000
Hey, 'afternoon.
You must be Shannon.

41:42.000 --> 41:44.402
Yeah. Can I help you?

41:44.402 --> 41:46.104
Uh... well, no.

41:46.104 --> 41:48.273
M... my name's pj.
I was sent down by Terry

41:48.273 --> 41:50.275
to let you know
that your car's ready.

41:50.275 --> 41:52.811
It's... is as good as gold.

41:52.811 --> 41:54.780
So whenever you wanna go down.

41:54.780 --> 41:57.148
We'll be down in a few minutes.
Thank you.

42:01.753 --> 42:03.154
Okie doke.

42:04.255 --> 42:05.924
Okay, then.

42:12.263 --> 42:13.799
Wow.

42:13.799 --> 42:17.402
Apparently, it is kosher in kain

42:17.402 --> 42:20.939
to give guest room numbers
to members of the public.

42:20.939 --> 42:22.307
That's awesome.

42:24.409 --> 42:26.778
Are you gonna make it, kid?

42:26.778 --> 42:29.414
Yeah.

42:29.414 --> 42:32.417
I just need a few minutes
to get my life together.

42:32.417 --> 42:33.952
All right.

42:33.952 --> 42:36.154
I'll clean up
and take care of the car.

42:49.801 --> 42:52.137
Oh, hey. That was quick.

42:52.137 --> 42:54.806
Yeah. We gotta hit the road.

42:56.808 --> 42:58.810
I'm sorry. Could you
tell me what time it is?

42:58.810 --> 43:00.178
My phone is dead.

43:00.178 --> 43:03.882
Ah, I think it's just
after 4:00 o'clock.

43:03.882 --> 43:05.383
4:00?

43:05.383 --> 43:07.185
No Jesus fucking way.

43:07.185 --> 43:09.921
- Pardon me?
- I'm sorry.

43:09.921 --> 43:11.256
Never mind.

43:11.256 --> 43:14.392
Um, is Terry around?

43:14.392 --> 43:15.927
No.

43:15.927 --> 43:17.929
He's still out in the truck.

43:17.929 --> 43:19.264
Okay. Uh,

43:19.264 --> 43:21.800
how much do I owe you, I guess?

43:21.800 --> 43:23.701
He left a note.

43:26.337 --> 43:28.239
Girls are all paid up.

43:30.876 --> 43:32.911
No, I don't think so.

43:32.911 --> 43:34.946
I think it's your lucky day.

43:36.481 --> 43:39.184
Yeah, I guess.

43:39.184 --> 43:40.952
Do you know when
Terry will be back, though?

43:40.952 --> 43:43.154
I'd like to thank him
for his help with everything.

43:43.154 --> 43:45.857
He just stepped out. He's gotta be
back for church and everything.

43:45.857 --> 43:47.192
Church? I'm sorry.

43:47.192 --> 43:49.494
Is it 4:00 o'clock on Sunday?

43:49.494 --> 43:50.929
No, ma'am, it's Saturday.

43:50.929 --> 43:53.198
But we so church
seven days a week here.

43:53.198 --> 43:54.365
So...

43:54.365 --> 43:56.434
That is a lot of churching.

43:58.503 --> 44:01.739
Okay. I guess, thanks again.

44:06.044 --> 44:08.880
Ma'am, you okay?

44:08.880 --> 44:11.516
Yeah, just, uh, have a headache.

44:11.516 --> 44:13.384
Why don't you head on over
to the supply store,

44:13.384 --> 44:15.286
fix it up?

44:15.286 --> 44:17.488
Thanks. I'll do that.

44:18.824 --> 44:20.859
Hangover's a bitch.

44:26.231 --> 44:28.233
Yeah.

44:28.233 --> 44:29.500
How did you...?

44:29.500 --> 44:31.502
On the count
of the bottles, ma'am,

44:31.502 --> 44:33.104
in your room.

44:35.907 --> 44:37.809
Got a good look
in there, did you?

44:56.261 --> 45:00.165
And kill me now.

45:31.129 --> 45:33.498
Uh, could I also grab
some ibuprophen?

45:38.603 --> 45:40.171
Thanks.

46:03.161 --> 46:04.896
Hello!

46:14.172 --> 46:15.907
Hello.

46:20.511 --> 46:22.080
Mack?

46:32.357 --> 46:34.392
Anybody home?

46:39.197 --> 46:40.698
Kris?

46:40.698 --> 46:43.568
You scared me.

46:43.568 --> 46:45.136
Slow day for you guys?

46:45.136 --> 46:47.138
Uh...

46:47.138 --> 46:49.574
Yeah, we usually don't get
much business during the day.

46:49.574 --> 46:51.309
I can see that.

46:55.546 --> 46:58.049
Um...

46:58.049 --> 46:59.384
What're you still doing here?

46:59.384 --> 47:00.718
We're getting ready to leave.

47:00.718 --> 47:03.721
I just figured
I'd come say goodbye.

47:03.721 --> 47:07.192
To thank you
for your hospitality.

47:07.192 --> 47:09.927
Sure. It was my pleasure.

47:13.398 --> 47:15.266
Okay.

47:15.266 --> 47:16.734
Well, I didn't mean
to disturb you.

47:16.734 --> 47:19.470
I'll let you get back
to work or whatever.

47:21.606 --> 47:23.174
Hey.

47:28.246 --> 47:30.248
You're a great girl.

47:30.248 --> 47:31.582
I'm sorry you have to leave.

47:31.582 --> 47:34.719
But, my advice...

47:37.122 --> 47:38.489
Drive like the wind.

47:40.091 --> 47:41.459
I always do.

47:45.730 --> 47:47.298
Bye, mack.

48:03.614 --> 48:05.350
What's with the pictures?

48:06.617 --> 48:08.353
Oh, whenever people move here

48:08.353 --> 48:10.455
we like to throw them a party.

48:10.455 --> 48:12.757
It's the neighborly thing to do.

48:20.765 --> 48:23.601
- Where are Terry and mack?
- They were the first ones here.

48:23.601 --> 48:26.537
No one was here
to take their picture.

48:26.537 --> 48:28.106
Hmm.

48:29.474 --> 48:31.209
Thanks.

48:37.582 --> 48:40.585
Hey, hey, hey. You're alive.

48:40.585 --> 48:43.788
- Barely.
- What'd you get me?

48:43.788 --> 48:45.756
Hah. For what ailes you.

48:45.756 --> 48:47.525
You're an angel.

48:47.525 --> 48:49.527
Did you go say bye
to your boyfriend?

48:49.527 --> 48:51.062
Indeed.

48:51.062 --> 48:52.397
Star-crossed lovers.

48:52.397 --> 48:54.265
That gets me every time.

48:54.265 --> 48:56.301
Shut it.

48:57.668 --> 49:00.338
Wait.

49:00.338 --> 49:02.773
What is that?

49:02.773 --> 49:05.576
That sounds like a party...

49:05.576 --> 49:07.178
No.

49:07.178 --> 49:10.515
- That I'm gonna go to.
- No party please.

49:10.515 --> 49:12.783
No party.

49:21.826 --> 49:24.529
- She's here!
- Emma Jean!

49:24.529 --> 49:27.098
- Hi.
- Oh, hi.

49:27.098 --> 49:30.868
What did I tell you about gettin'
up in peoples personal space?

49:30.868 --> 49:32.737
Some people don't like it.

49:32.737 --> 49:35.440
- That's right.
- It's really okay.

49:35.440 --> 49:38.476
I have a lot of nieces and
nephews back home. So...

49:38.476 --> 49:41.212
I gave up on personal space
a long time ago.

49:41.212 --> 49:43.781
You still have to mind
your manners.

49:43.781 --> 49:45.783
Yes, ma'am.

49:45.783 --> 49:47.352
You must be Emma Jean's mom?

49:47.352 --> 49:48.686
No, ma'am.

49:48.686 --> 49:50.855
I just look after her
from time to time.

49:50.855 --> 49:52.723
Oh. Then where is she?

49:52.723 --> 49:55.426
Emma Jean!

49:55.426 --> 49:58.129
- What're you guys celebrating?
- Excuse me?

49:58.129 --> 50:00.365
Just seems like some kind
of backyard party.

50:00.365 --> 50:03.701
Minus the grilling and a yard.

50:03.701 --> 50:05.870
No, it's... it's not a party.

50:05.870 --> 50:08.539
We do this everyday.

50:08.539 --> 50:11.442
It's our way of keeping
in touch, I guess.

50:11.442 --> 50:13.878
Kind of like a family.

50:13.878 --> 50:15.613
You guys don't have jobs?

50:15.613 --> 50:18.249
Some folks do.

50:18.249 --> 50:20.418
Most don't need to.

50:20.418 --> 50:22.887
Mostly everything's
provided for us here.

50:22.887 --> 50:25.423
So then, what do you do all day?

50:25.423 --> 50:27.292
Well...

50:27.292 --> 50:29.460
This.

50:29.460 --> 50:30.795
And, in a few minutes,

50:30.795 --> 50:32.897
Terry will start
the daily service.

50:32.897 --> 50:34.899
He's the boss.

50:34.899 --> 50:36.401
Oh, is that right?

50:36.401 --> 50:37.802
Sure is.

50:40.271 --> 50:43.274
It seems like, uh,
nice enough kind of guy.

50:43.274 --> 50:44.609
Yes.

50:48.646 --> 50:50.515
Time for mass.

50:50.515 --> 50:52.850
I guess y'all better be
on your way now.

50:52.850 --> 50:55.386
- Come along, Emma Jean.
- But...

50:55.386 --> 50:57.188
Y'all drive safe now.

51:05.230 --> 51:07.632
Ladies.

51:07.632 --> 51:09.634
Oh, hey.

51:09.634 --> 51:10.968
I'm really glad
we ran into you, actually.

51:10.968 --> 51:12.770
I wanted to say
thanks for your help

51:12.770 --> 51:15.706
with the car and everything
before we hit...

51:15.706 --> 51:17.242
The road.

51:17.242 --> 51:19.410
Of course.

51:19.410 --> 51:21.579
I don't suppose I could tempt
you with a little churching

51:21.579 --> 51:23.514
before you head on your way?

51:23.514 --> 51:25.416
Um...

51:26.817 --> 51:28.653
No. I'm sorry.

51:28.653 --> 51:31.956
We would love to but we should
probably get going.

51:31.956 --> 51:34.825
Thank you, though.

51:34.825 --> 51:37.528
Did, uh... Did pj not tell you?

51:37.528 --> 51:40.531
There's no charge
on the repairs?

51:40.531 --> 51:41.966
Um, he did.

51:41.966 --> 51:43.834
I... I appreciate that.

51:43.834 --> 51:46.371
Well then, don't you think
it's the least you can do?

